Require the LGU personnel to submit a copy of print-out DTR from biometric device for CY 2016 as proof of their attendance;

Issue a certification that the activities/services cannot be provided by regular or permanent personnel of the agency before employing job orders/contract of service personnel; 

Require each payees to prepare individual accomplishment report duly verified and signed by the immediate supervisor;

Refrain from submitting a duplicate/scan copy of DTR and Accomplishment Report;

Indicate the number and date of their CTCs as a required identification on the payroll;

Indicate the statement of duties and responsibilities of each personnel; and 

Evaluate the necessity of getting the services of job orders and consider terminating those services whose functions are redundant to the functions of the different officers and/or offices in order that unnecessary expenditures be minimize, if not totally avoided.

Conduct a periodic physical inventory of supplies or property semestrally as required under Section 124 of Manual on NGAS for LGU;

Maintain stock cards and supplied ledger card for each type of supplies;

Record and issue supplies and materials following the perpetual inventory method as prescribed under Sections 114, 116 and 121 of the NGAS for LGUs; and 

Require the Municipal Accountant to revert back to Office Supplies Inventory and Drugs and Medicines Inventory account the amount of ₱690,962.47 and ₱3,100,592.60 respectively or collate any available records/documents that would be the basis of the Accounting Office in dropping from the books of the Municipality the non-existing Office Supplies Inventory and Drugs and Medicines Inventory.

Strictly adhere to the provisions of R.A. 9003 and implement the 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan they had prepared and allot a budget for the program; 

As a first step, put up receptacles that are well categorized and segregated and immediately take a comprehensive program to address garbage disposal that would ultimately eliminate the existing practice; and

Take appropriate actions that would lead to the closure of the open dump and switch to sanitary landfill.

